# =============================================================================
# .dockerignore
# =============================================================================
#
# Every service Dockerfile uses `context: ..` from docker/compose.dev.yml,
# which means the ENTIRE workspace ships to the daemon per build. Without
# this ignore file that's ~4 GB of node_modules + vendor + .git + build
# artefacts — kills iteration speed.
#
# Docker's ignore syntax matches `.gitignore` — one pattern per line, `!`
# to negate. Patterns are relative to the build context root
# (the workspace root, since `context: ..`).
#
# ## What we EXCLUDE
#
# Everything a container doesn't need at build time:
#   * VCS metadata (.git, .git/)
#   * Composer / npm caches + installed deps (vendor/, node_modules/)
#   * Editor / OS junk (.DS_Store, .vscode/, .idea/, Thumbs.db)
#   * Local doppler state (.doppler/)
#   * Test snapshots + coverage reports
#   * Frontend build outputs (dist/, public/build/, public/hot/)
#   * Bootstrap caches (bootstrap/cache/ — the container regenerates them)
#   * Storage runtime dirs (logs, sessions, views — always regenerated)
#
# ## What we DON'T exclude
#
# Everything Composer + Laravel need at boot:
#   * Every composer.json + composer.lock (path-repo resolution)
#   * Every src/ + bootstrap/ + config/ + database/
#   * docker/ (the Dockerfile itself)
#
# ## Sanity check
#
# After editing, verify: `docker build ...` shows the build-context
# transfer at <200 MB, not 4 GB.

# ── VCS ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.git/
.git*
!.gitignore
!.gitattributes
!.github/

# ── Dep + build artefacts ──────────────────────────────────────────
**/vendor/
**/node_modules/
**/dist/
**/build/
**/.turbo/

# ── Composer + npm caches ──────────────────────────────────────────
.composer/
.npm/

# ── Editor / OS ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.DS_Store
.vscode/
.idea/
.zed/
.nova/
.cursor/
.codex/
.phpactor.json
Thumbs.db

# ── Test artefacts ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
**/.phpunit.cache/
**/.phpunit.result.cache
**/coverage/
**/.pest-cache/

# ── Doppler local state (never bake secrets into images) ───────────
.doppler/
**/.doppler/

# ── Laravel runtime dirs ───────────────────────────────────────────
**/bootstrap/cache/*
!**/bootstrap/cache/.gitignore
**/storage/logs/*
!**/storage/logs/.gitignore
**/storage/framework/cache/data/*
**/storage/framework/sessions/*
!**/storage/framework/sessions/.gitignore
**/storage/framework/views/*
!**/storage/framework/views/.gitignore
**/storage/pail
**/storage/*.key

# ── Front-end build outputs ────────────────────────────────────────
**/public/build/
**/public/hot
**/public/fonts-manifest.dev.json
**/public/storage

# ── Kiro state (not needed inside containers) ──────────────────────
.kiro/settings/mcp.json
.kiro/hooks/
.kiro/agents/
.kiro/specs/
# Keep .kiro/reports/ — the CI job runs the audit scripts there.
!.kiro/reports/
# Keep .kiro/steering/ — reviewers look at rules; also referenced by docs.
!.kiro/steering/

# ── Refs, historical ──────────────────────────────────────────────
.ref/
old/

# ── Frontend workspace nooks (we don't build the frontend in the PHP images) ──
packages/frontend/
apps/react-native-template/
apps/vite-template/

# ── Ignore Dockerfiles + compose from OTHER contexts leaking in ──
# (the build context still needs docker/service.Dockerfile itself)
